The morphological properties of the as-produced Cu-based oxide nanostructures were resolved by FESEM and TEM analysis. As depicted in Fig. 4, the non-uniform flaky shapes with multiple layers dominate the overall morphology prepared at the highest reaction temperature (80 °C) with pH 11. The average mean particle diameter, dm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
